    {
      "href": "/joelbar/list/minimalist-cinema/",
      "user": "joelbar",
      "slug": "minimalist-cinema",
      "title": "Minimalist cinema",
      "desc": "I believe in the power of minimalism in filmmaking so I made this list to see if my average rating agrees with that statement.\n\nIt's a bit subjective, but I would describe a minimalistic movie as one that doesn't stand out in any technical aspect (little to no vfx, small cast and limited space, a soundtrack that feels like it's not even there, if there even is one, a simple story,...) and sometimes feels nice to watch without the audience really knowing why.\n\nIt can also just be a movie that makes you feel like they could've done so much more with it but ultimately they didn't (and maybe that worked).",
      "owner": "List by Joel",
      "tags": []
    },
