    {
      "href": "/kenoticdreams/list/contemplative-minimalist-cinema/",
      "user": "kenoticdreams",
      "slug": "contemplative-minimalist-cinema",
      "title": "Contemplative & Minimalist Cinema",
      "desc": "Wallace Stevens said that \"we ought to like poetry the same way that children like snow\", but I think the same might be said of contemplative cinema.\n\nThese are films in which the image or duration of empty, liminal spaces take the role of the protagonist; which through their absence of typical narrative constructs invite their viewers to participate in a meditative appreciation of the present moment.\n\nThese films could easily be passed over as needlessly pretentious, and some may well be. But I think the exact opposite is most often true. At their best, contemplative films can rewaken us to a sense of awe at the existence of the world, and at our existence in it; an experience of stepping into a world re-imagined. Who needs drama when you have a sunset?",
      "owner": "List by Jonny Rogers",
